    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/evidence/multi-study-hemolysis-synthesis",
      "type": "uofa:Evidence",
      "name": "Synthesis of multiple prior hemolysis CFD validation studies",
      "description": "This evidence node represents a comprehensive synthesis of twelve prior hemolysis CFD validation studies published between 2005 and 2022, including the seminal Giersiepen-Wurzinger experimental calibration dataset, the Taskin et al. FDA pump benchmark results, the Hariharan et al. round-robin inter-laboratory comparison, and nine additional independent validation exercises spanning axial and centrifugal pump geometries. The synthesis documents consistent model performance across a wide range of operating conditions and pump designs, providing strong qualitative support for the claim that the power-law hemolysis damage model generalizes to centrifugal VAD geometries. The aggregated evidence base represents the community consensus on achievable CFD hemolysis prediction accuracy."
    },
